## Setting up the project

I already had a SvelteKit project set up (this one you are reading right now [mateux.dev](https://mateux.dev). However, I came in blind on how could I implement my idea and requirements. After some roadblocks, Proof of Concept and some research, I found a way to implement my idea. And here we are, I am writing my first blog post using SvelteKit and Markdown files.

To get started, if you don't have a SvelteKit project yet, you can create one using the following command:

```bash
bunx sv create my-blog
```

Set it up with your preferred options. Once you have your SvelteKit project ready, we can start adding the necessary components to support Markdown files and Mermaid diagrams.


